sequenceDiagram
    participant KFTO as KFTO PyTorchJob<br/>Controller
    participant Pod as Training Pod<br/>(accelerate_launch.py)
    participant SFT as sft_trainer.py<br/>(SFTTrainer)
    participant PVC as PVC Storage<br/>(model + data + output)
    participant GPU as NVIDIA GPU<br/>(CUDA)
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Tracker as Experiment Tracker<br/>(Aim/MLflow/ClearML)
    participant NCCL as NCCL/Gloo<br/>29500/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over KFTO,Pod: Flow 1: Training Job Execution
        KFTO->>Pod: Create training pod<br/>Kubernetes API / TLS 1.3<br/>ServiceAccount auth
        Pod->>Pod: Parse JSON config<br/>(SFT_TRAINER_CONFIG_JSON_PATH)
        Pod->>SFT: subprocess: accelerate launch<br/>sft_trainer.py
        SFT->>PVC: Load model weights<br/>Local filesystem mount
        PVC-->>SFT: Model artifacts
        SFT->>PVC: Load training data<br/>Local filesystem mount
        PVC-->>SFT: Training dataset
        SFT->>HF: Download model/tokenizer (fallback)<br/>HTTPS/443 / TLS 1.2+<br/>Bearer Token (HF_TOKEN)
        HF-->>SFT: Pre-trained weights
        SFT->>GPU: Training computation<br/>PCIe/NVLink
        GPU-->>SFT: Gradients & loss
        SFT->>Tracker: Push metrics<br/>HTTP(S) / configurable
        SFT->>PVC: Save checkpoints & output<br/>Local filesystem mount
        SFT->>Pod: Training complete
        Pod->>Pod: Write /dev/termination-log<br/>(exit code 0/1/203)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Pod,NCCL: Flow 2: Multi-GPU FSDP Training
        Pod->>Pod: Detect GPU count<br/>torch.cuda.device_count()
        Pod->>NCCL: Initialize process group<br/>TCP/29500 (plaintext)
        NCCL-->>Pod: Rendezvous complete
        loop Each FSDP Rank
            Pod->>GPU: Shard model parameters<br/>PCIe/NVLink
            GPU->>NCCL: All-reduce gradients<br/>NCCL (plaintext)
            NCCL-->>GPU: Synchronized gradients
        end
        Pod->>PVC: Save consolidated checkpoint<br/>(rank 0 only)
    end
